==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fascine
<hw>Fas*cine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>fascina</ets> a bundle of sticks, fr. <ets>fascis</ets>. See
<er>Fasces</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort. & Engin.)</fld> <def>A cylindrical
bundle of small sticks of wood, bound together, used in raising
batteries, filling ditches, strengthening ramparts, and making parapets;
also in revetments for river banks, and in mats for dams, jetties,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fascinous</ent>⟦br⟧
